The paper focuses on network embeddings, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically considers textual networks, which suggests that it may also fall under "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The use of a variational autoencoder and homophilic prior design also suggests that the paper may fall under "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) and "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval), respectively. Finally, the paper's focus on improving downstream task performance suggests that it may also fall under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence).
